A shoemaker is often influenced by many a strangers. Particularly those who do not know the shoemaker by heart. In ancient Greece, shoemaking was considered slothful and unwise, but the Romans took great pride in their shoemakers. As time has progressed, shoemaking has steadfastly been replaced by machines. What once was a true godly art perfected by the Romans, has now become nothing more than a dream lofting on a cloud on high.